text: Tandel is a commune in Luxembourg. It is part of the canton of Vianden. As of 2019, 2,083 people live here. The commune was created on 1 January 2006 from the former communes of Bastendorf (in the canton of Diekirch) and Fouhren (in the canton of Vianden).
